SUMMARY:Samuel Valach (Trinity College Dublin / Coláiste na Tríonóide, Baile Átha Cliath), Thermal Correlators, Holography and Black Hole Singularity
DESCRIPTION:Black hole singularities in AdS are reflected in the so‐called bouncing geodesics. In the dual CFT this leads to the bouncing singularities in the thermal correlators. I will explain both sides of this problem and show how these singularities arise from the analytic properties of the stress tensor and its composites in the boundary CFT.
UID:SamuelValach20241002@hertsmathphys.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260413T162346Z
