DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250409T150000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250409T160000
SUMMARY:Alexandros Spyridion Arvanitakis Αλέξανδρος Σπυριδίων Αρβανιτάκης (Institut Ruđer Bošković), Non‐invertible symmetries &amp; lagrangian correspondences in Chern–Simons theory
DESCRIPTION:I will discuss my recent work on a symplectic‐geometrical realisation of non‐invertible symmetries (alias codimension 1 topological defects) and its application to Chern–Simons theory. In particular my collaborators and I have constructed non‐invertible symmetries in non‐abelian Chern–Simons theory using a Yang–Baxter type equation from the theory of integrable systems, and we have found a novel and simple kind of non-invertibility even in abelian Chern–Simons theory, based on the mathematical structure of a semigroup.
UID:AlexandrosSpyridionArvanitakisΑλέξανδροςΣπυριδίωνΑρβανιτάκης20250409@hertsmathphys.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260413T162346Z
