DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20220324T133000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20220324T143000
SUMMARY:Pietro Benetti Genolini (King’s College London), Localization of the action in AdS/CFT
DESCRIPTION:I will introduce a simple formula for the action of supersymmetric solutions to minimal gauged supergravity in the context of the AdS/CFT correspondence. Such solutions are equipped with a Killing vector, and I will show that the holographically renormalized action may be expressed entirely in terms of the weights of this vector field at its fixed points, together with certain topological data. In this sense, the classical gravitational partition function localizes in the bulk, and depends only on the topology of the fixed point set.
UID:PietroBenettiGenolini20220324@hertsmathphys.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260413T162346Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
SEQUENCE:0
