SUMMARY:Katarzyna Anna Rejzner (University of York), Symmetries in mathematical perturbative quantum field theory
DESCRIPTION:In this talk I will give an overview of (perturbative) algebraic quantum field theory and explain how it can be applied to describe interacting QFT models. I will then report on new progress in the description of renormalization group and symmetries, using nets of C*‐algebras.
