DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20230222T133000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20230222T143000
SUMMARY:Cheuk Yu Mak 麥焯如 (University of Southampton), Quantum cohomology and loop group action
DESCRIPTION:Quantum cohomology is an invariant of symplectic manifolds. It is a commutative deformation of theusual cohomology as an algebra, where the deformation is controlled by counting certain holomorphic spheres. In this talk, we will first explain how it is related to the loop space, and to Floer cohomology. Then we will sketch that,in the presence of a Hamiltonian 𝐺‐action on a symplectic manifold 𝑀 with acompact Lie group 𝐺,  how we can obtain an action on the 𝐺‐‐equivariant quantum cohomology from the 𝐺‐equivariant Borel–Moore homology of the based loop space of 𝐺. No knowledge on symplectic geometry is assumed. This is a joint work with Eduardo González and Dan Pomerleano.
UID:CheukYuMak麥焯如20230222@hertsmathphys.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260413T162346Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
SEQUENCE:0
