DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20230322T160000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20230322T170000
SUMMARY:Arthur Lipstein (Durham University), From amplitudes to cosmology
DESCRIPTION:Whereas scattering amplitudes probe physics at the shortest distances, cosmology probes physics at the largest scales. Nevertheless, many concepts discovered in the study of scattering amplitudes generalise to cosmological observables. In this talk I will describe some aspects of this program which I have recently been investigating such as the double copy, scattering equations, and soft limits, and will discuss how these directions are interrelated.
UID:ArthurLipstein20230322@hertsmathphys.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260413T162346Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
