SUMMARY:Fabian Hahner (University of Washington), A supergeometric approach to (twisted) eleven-dimensional supergravity
DESCRIPTION:I will present a geometric perspective on superspace that proves fruitful for studying twisted supergravity, especially in eleven dimensions. This allows for a uniform description of the eleven-dimensional theory and its twists in terms of homotopy Poisson-Chern-Simons theory on appropriate superspaces. If time permits, I will further discuss higher symmetries in twisted supergravity theories and how they hint towards interesting global structures.
