SUMMARY:Devon Stockall (University of Southern Denmark), Continuous categorical gauging and symmetry breaking
DESCRIPTION:In the case of finite group G, the symmetries of 2d G gauge theories can be obtained using fusion categories and "higher representation-theoretic" methods.  However, gauge theories that appear in physics make use of Lie group symmetry.  In this talk, I will give a dictionary between gauge theory and category theory, and show how the fusion-categorical approach to gauge theory can be extended to recover the symmetries of flat continuous gauge theories in arbitrary dimension.
