SUMMARY:Paula Pilatus (University of Hamburg), Geometry of EFT positivity constraints
DESCRIPTION:Positivity bounds are theoretical constraints on the Wilson coefficients of an effective field theory. These bounds emerge from the requirement that a given effective field theory must be the low-energy limit of a relativistic quantum theory that satisfies the fundamental principles of unitarity, locality, and causality. In this talk we will discuss how the task of deriving (forward scattering) positivity bounds can be reformulated as the geometric problem of finding the extremal rays of a convex cone of four-tensors with certain symmetries. We will give the solution to this problem for scatterings involving up to three flavors. Finally, we will see how the positivity bounds obtained this way give rise to new constraints that are not already captured by elastic bounds and hence improve the known forward scattering positivity bounds from the literature. Based on arXiv:2508.18165. (slides)

UID:PaulaPilatus20260325@hertsmathphys.github.io
